WEST NILE VIRUS (03): AMERICAS (USA)
************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Sun 5 Jul 2020
Source: Fox News [edited]
https://www.foxnews.com/health/miami-dade-county-west-nile-virus-residents


Health officials in Miami-Dade County, Florida, on Saturday [4 Jul 2020] confirmed that at least 18 people living in the county have contracted the West Nile virus.

The latest figures followed the county's mosquito-control chief's comments last week that this summer's [2020] resurgence of West Nile probably reflected the heavy rains that have caused mosquito populations to explode, the Miami Herald reported. More mosquitoes have meant more mosquito bites, increasing the odds of infection.

The county was under a mosquito-borne-illness alert. The health department reported West Nile virus has been the leading cause of mosquito-borne disease in the United States. Doctors have warned there were no vaccines [for humans] to prevent it or medications to treat it.

Miami-Dade's 1st 2 cases of West Nile virus in the current outbreak were detected in May [2020]. On 11 Jun [2020], health officials reported 2 more cases of the virus. On 25 Jun [2020], 10 more residents were confirmed to have the virus.

[Byline: Bradford Betz]

